{
  "texts": [
    "Also in Montessori, as in the AIF, the cognitive life starts early, in the womb, to which she refers to as \"psycho-embryonal life\" (e.g.,Montessori, 2023.",
    "The similarity of these ideas with the well-known \"genetic epistemology\" of Jean Piaget, that some readers might notice, should not surprise.",
    "Piaget had done is first observations in a Montessori school and attended at least one of Maria Montessori's classes for educators(Lillard, 2017: 27; Kramer, 2017; O´Donnell, 2012).",
    "Most importantly, Piaget was for many years the president of the Swiss Montessori Society (e.g., Hofstetter & Schneuwly, 2022).",
    "It is worth noticing, however, that while Piaget's theory of development is a series of discrete stages, for Montessori development is a continuous, in which \"each level descends from the previous one and in turn prepares the next\"(Tornar, 2023."
  ]
}